{"title": "Bee-Keeping For All", "description": "Originally published by a master bee-keeper in 1923, this 3rd edition of \u2018Bee-Keeping For All\u2019 was completely revised (in 1929) and brought up to date to reflect at that time the advance in knowledge and practical improvements in all aspects of bee-keeping work that would have usefully concerned the average small hive-owner or those with whom honey and wax production formed only one activity among many areas of their business.\r\nAs a lifelong bee-keeper Tickner Edwardes shares his extensive practical understanding and in-depth knowledge of apiculture with details of how to set up and manage and develop a successful apiary and how to avoid the many potential problems that could be encountered.\r\nAlso, you will find it well worth checking out the ebook of \u2018Bee-Keeping For All\u2019 to view the numerous detailed plans and graphics that accompany and compliment the text of this book. \r\nA similar book (\u2018Bee-Keeping Do\u2019s and Dont\u2019s\u2019) by Tickner Edwardes that compliments this publication is also available in ebook and audiobook formats.\r\n - Summary by Steve C", "duration": 24699, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "11276", "name": "Tickner Edwardes"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/beekeepingforall_2506_librivox/beekeeping_all_2506.jpg", "copyright_year": "1929", "genres": ["Nature"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Steve C"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Steve C"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Front Matter", "readers": [7389], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/beekeepingforall_2506_librivox/beekeepingforall_00_edwardes_64kb.mp3", "duration": 458}, {"section": 1, "title": "Early Considerations In Bee-Craft", "readers": [7389], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/beekeepingforall_2506_librivox/beekeepingforall_01_edwardes_64kb.mp3",